      "code_changes": [
        {
          "content": "{\n  \"files\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"expressjs-express\",\n      \"path\": \"lib/request.js\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"expressjs-express\",\n      \"path\": \"test/req.host.js\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"expressjs-express\",\n      \"path\": \"History.md\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"text\": \"The deprecated `req.host` property is referenced in three files within the expressjs-express repository:\\n\\n1. **lib/request.js (line 418)**: Contains the definition of the deprecated `req.host` getter. This getter returns the Host header value including the port number (e.g., 'example.com:3000'). It respects the 'trust proxy' setting and can read from the 'X-Forwarded-Host' header when proxy trust is enabled. The getter is implemented using Object.defineProperty with a function that returns the host value or undefined.\\n\\n2. **test/req.host.js**: Contains a comprehensive test suite specifically for the `req.host` property. The tests verify various behaviors including: basic Host header parsing, returning undefined when no Host is present, handling IPv6 addresses in brackets, respecting X-Forwarded-Host when 'trust proxy' is enabled, and handling different trust proxy configurations. The test file contains 10 references to `req.host` across multiple test cases.\\n\\n3. **History.md**: Contains multiple changelog entries documenting the history of `req.host`, including:\\n   - The original addition of the `req.host` property\\n   - Multiple fixes for `req.host` behavior (IPv6 support, trust proxy fixes, X-Forwarded-Host support)\\n   - The deprecation of `req.host` in favor of `req.hostname` (which returns only the hostname without the port)\\n   - A note that `req.host` now returns host with port (hostname:port format) while `req.hostname` is the correct property for getting only the hostname\\n\\nThe `req.hostname` getter (defined at line 444 in lib/request.js) depends on `req.host` by calling `this.host` and extracting just the hostname portion without the port, which is why it's the recommended replacement for the deprecated `req.host` property when only the hostname is needed.\"\n}\n",
          "file_path": "/workspace/answer.json",
          "sequence": 30,
          "type": "write"
        }
      ],
